<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Resume summary</title>
    <%- include("shared/links"); %>
    <style>
        body {  
            /* background: #121212; */
            color: white;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
        }
        .navbar {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #0062E6, #33AEFF);
        }
        .navbar-brand {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 28px;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }
        .btn{
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 10px 23px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        #logoutButton {
            background-color: #dc3545;
            color: white;
            border: none;
        }
        .summary{
            border: 2px solid cadetblue;
            border-radius: 24px;   
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Header -->
    <%- include("shared/header", {loggedin : isAuth}); %>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="summary mt-5">
            <div class="summary text-black p-4">
                <p><%= summary %></p>
                <!-- A Senior Machine Learning Engineer specializes in creating, deploying, and maintaining advanced machine learning models that drive innovation and efficiency within software applications.
                They leverage their deep understanding of machine learning, natural language processing, and data science to develop algorithms that can learn from and make decisions based on data.
                This role involves a blend of technical expertise, creativity, and problem-solving skills to tackle complex challenges in various domains, including search and recommendation systems. -->
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="d-flex gap-3 mt-5">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="gotoPreviewPage()">Preview page</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning" onclick="gotoSkillsPage()">Previous page</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="regenerate()">Re-genereate</button>
        </div>
    </div>
   
    <script src="/js/summary.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
